<HEAD>
<TITLE>PackIt - History</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>History</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>0.1 First Beta Release - July 2010</B></LI>
<LI><B>0.2 Second Beta Release - February 2011</B></LI>
<UL>
<LI>Added missing IconSprites line to !Run file</LI>
<LI>Set file types for HTML help files</LI>
<LI>Fixed typo in sysvars documentation</LI>
<LI>Maximum length of sprite name in edit sprite dialogue increased from
11 to 12 characters</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: File type was packaged as 000 for Image Filing System files</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: After reloading, modifying and changing a package it could fail to save and would corrupt the package file</LI>
<LI>Show nicer dialogue when the package load fails.<LI>
<LI>Stop extra (harmless) error messages being shown when a load fails<LI>
</UL>
</LI>
<LI><B>0.3 Third Beta Release - September 2011</B></LI>
<UL>
<LI>Bugfix: Fields on the Depends tab were not being updated if they were selected from the menu</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: Dependencies menus were left empty after the first package processed was closed</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: System variables were not always redisplayed correctly when a package we reloaded</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: It was impossible to add a system variable that included a hyphen</LI>
<LI>Bugfix: Scanning boot files for system variables did not remove quotes if the variable value was quoted which stopped them being set correctly by the package manager</LI>
<LI>Boot file scanning for system variables will now pick out variables from If statements if the If variable and the Set variable are the same</LI>
<LI>Boot file scanning now replaces the argument substitution "%%*0" from variables with "%*0" so the immediate set of the variable by the package manager will work</LI>
</UL>

<LI><B>0.4 Fourth Beta Release - February 2012</B></LI>
<UL>
<LI>Remove button on System variables tab did not update the package</LI>
</UL>

</UL>

</BODY>
</HTML>
